 Java8 Date and Time

  1- Immutability: ex date class is mutable and this is one of biggest problem with date and calendar class. But with java8 is immutable is good for multithread envs.
  2- Separation of Concerns: The new API separates clearly between human readable date time and machine time(unix timestamp)
  3- Clarity
  4- Utility Ops
  5- Extendable


 // java8 date time consists of following packages;
 // java.time package: base package of new date time API. LocalDate, LocalTime, LocalDateTime, Instant, Period and Duration. All of these are immutable
 // java.time.chrono package: This package defines generic APIs for non ISO calendar systems.
 // java.time.format
 // java.time.temporal
 // java.time.zone